fno: Turnover on the National Stock Exchange's futures & options (F&O) segment was Rs 282.61 lakh crore compared with Rs 178.55 lakh crore reported in the previous session. In the cash market, the Nifty 50 shed 45.85 points or 0.26% to settle at 17,616.30. The NSE's India VIX, a gauge of market's expectation of volatility over the near term, declined 0.56% to 16.78. Adani Ports and Special Economic Zone, ICICI Bank, Adani Enterprises were the top traded individual stock futures contracts in F&O segment of NSE. The February 2023 F&O contracts will expire on 23 February 2023.
